  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Preset Profiles</h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Preset profiles are named bundles of routing categories. When applied, they automatically assign the best available model (ranked by benchmark score for the category's primary capability axis) to each category in the bundle.</p>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The assignment is <strong class="text-white/80">non-destructive</strong>: categories that already have a <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">defaultModel</code> configured are skipped.</p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full border-collapse">
      <thead><tr><th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Profile</th><th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Category focus</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">software_development</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Code generation, debugging, refactoring, security review, DevOps</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">customer_support</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">FAQ, sentiment analysis, summarisation, instruction following</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">research_analysis</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Data analysis, STEM, long context, formal reasoning</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">creative_content</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Brainstorming, copywriting, proofreading, format conversion</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">data_operations</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">SQL, data transformation, API integration, QA testing</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">agentic_workflows</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Agentic SWE, function calling, multi-step tool use</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">general_all</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">All 45 categories — full coverage</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Profiles are selectable in the <strong class="text-white/80">Setup Wizard</strong> (step 2 of 4) and re-applicable at any time via <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">POST /api/prism/admin/categories/apply-preset</code>.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Model Selection</h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Once a category and tier are determined, the model is selected as follows:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Category <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">defaultModel</code></strong> — if set, use it directly (highest priority)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Benchmark-weighted price-performance</strong> — within the target tier, all eligible models are scored using a weighted benchmark formula that considers the category's primary capability axes, combined with cost (see below)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Tenant routing <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">defaultModel</code></strong> — fallback if no category default and no benchmark data</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Context window check</strong> — if the selected model's context window is smaller than the estimated token count, escalate to the next larger model (<code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">findLargerContextModel</code>)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Context-aware tier upgrade</strong> — if <em>no</em> model in the selected tier can fit the estimated input tokens, the router automatically steps up through tiers (minimal &rarr; low &rarr; medium &rarr; high) until a model with sufficient context window is found. Logged as <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">context_tier_upgrade_&lt;tier&gt;</code> in the <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">override_applied</code> field.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Benchmark-Weighted Routing</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Instead of simply picking the cheapest model in a tier, Model Prism calculates a <strong class="text-white/80">price-performance score</strong> for each eligible model. The score combines benchmark quality with cost:</p>
  <pre class="bg-[#0d0d14] border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-white/70 mb-6 font-mono"><code>quality = (w_intelligence * intelligence) + (w_coding * coding) + (w_math * math) + (w_speed * speed)
cost    = inputPer1M + outputPer1M
score   = quality / cost^exponent</code></pre>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The benchmark weights are determined by the routing category:</p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Category type</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Intelligence</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Coding</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Math</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Speed</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">code_*</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.15</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.55</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.20</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.10</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">reasoning_*</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">math</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.25</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.10</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.55</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.10</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">summarization_*</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">translation</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.20</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.05</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.05</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.70</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Default (all others)</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.40</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.20</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.20</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.20</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">This means a coding task will strongly prefer models with high coding benchmarks, while a summarization task will prefer fast models — even within the same cost tier.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Cost Mode</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The <strong class="text-white/80">cost mode</strong> setting controls the balance between output quality and cost savings. It affects both <strong class="text-white/80">tier shifting</strong> (moving requests up or down a tier) and <strong class="text-white/80">model ranking within a tier</strong> (how aggressively cost is penalized in the price-performance formula).</p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Mode</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Cost exponent</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Tier shift</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Effect</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">economy</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">2.0</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Step down one tier</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Maximize savings — heavily penalizes expensive models, prefers cheapest options</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">balanced</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">1.0</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">No shift (default)</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Best price-performance ratio — equal weighting of quality and cost</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">quality</code></td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">0.3</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Step up one tier</td><td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Maximize output quality — cost is secondary, prefers highest-scoring models</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The cost exponent controls how much cost matters in the <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">quality / cost^exponent</code> formula. A higher exponent makes expensive models score much lower. At exponent 0.3 (quality mode), a model that costs 10x more only gets a 2x penalty — benchmark scores dominate the ranking.</p>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Cost mode is configured per rule set in the <strong class="text-white/80">Routing Config</strong> UI under "Cost Optimization Mode".</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Budget Guard Integration</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The <strong class="text-white/80">budget guard</strong> can automatically override the cost mode when spend approaches a configured threshold. When the guard activates:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Auto-routed requests</strong> — the cost mode is overridden to <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">economy</code>, which steps down one tier and heavily penalizes expensive models within the remaining tier. Results stay reasonable because the best cheap models are selected by benchmark score.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Explicit model requests</strong> — requests targeting a blocked tier (e.g. <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">high</code>) are still rejected with a <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">429</code> error.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">This means auto-routed traffic degrades gracefully instead of being cut off entirely. Configure the guard cost mode override per tenant under <strong class="text-white/80">Budget Guard &rarr; Auto-Route Cost Mode Override</strong>.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Response Enrichment</h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every auto-routed response includes routing metadata in the response body:</p>
  <pre class="bg-[#0d0d14] border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-white/70 mb-6 font-mono"><code>&#123;
  "choices": [...],
  "auto_routing": &#123;
    "category": "code_security_review",
    "confidence": 0.91,
    "complexity": "complex",
    "cost_tier": "high",
    "model_id": "claude-opus-4-6",
    "override_applied": "security_escalation",
    "analysis_time_ms": 312,
    "domain": "tech",
    "reasoning": "Request contains 3 security-related keyword patterns and 82k token codebase"
  &#125;,
  "cost_info": &#123;
    "actual_cost": 0.0187,
    "baseline_cost": 0.0210,
    "saved": 0.0023,
    "input_tokens": 82140,
    "output_tokens": 1820
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">If a context fallback occurred (model was upgraded due to context overflow), a <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">context_fallback</code> field is also included:</p>
  <pre class="bg-[#0d0d14] border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-white/70 mb-6 font-mono"><code>"context_fallback": &#123;
  "original_model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  "fallback_model": "claude-opus-4-6",
  "reason": "context_overflow"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Provider Fallback Chains
   
  </h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">When a provider returns an error, Model Prism can automatically fail over to an alternative provider using <strong class="text-white/80">fallback chains</strong>.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Circuit Breaker</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Each provider is monitored with a circuit breaker that transitions through three states:</p>
  <pre class="bg-[#0d0d14] border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-white/70 mb-6 font-mono"><code>CLOSED      normal operation — all requests forwarded
    ↓ error threshold exceeded
OPEN        provider marked down — requests skip to next in chain
    ↓ cooldown period elapsed
HALF_OPEN   probe requests sent — if successful, return to CLOSED</code></pre>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Per-Tenant Configuration</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Fallback chains are configurable per tenant, per model pattern or using a wildcard <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">'*'</code> to match all models. When a provider error occurs, the gateway automatically retries with the next provider in the chain.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Context-Aware Fallback</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">On context overflow errors, the fallback system automatically upgrades to a larger context model. The pre-flight context check uses the model registry as a fallback source for context window data when provider metadata is unavailable.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Webhook Notifications</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">When a provider transitions to <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">OPEN</code> (down), a <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">provider_down</code> webhook event is fired to notify administrators.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">A/B Testing for Routing
   
  </h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Model Prism supports <strong class="text-white/80">A/B testing experiments</strong> to compare routing strategies or model variants under real production traffic.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Experiment Model</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Each experiment defines weighted variants. Traffic is distributed across variants using <strong class="text-white/80">consistent session-based hashing</strong> (SHA-256) so that the same session always hits the same variant.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Per-Variant Metrics</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Each variant tracks:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Requests</strong> — total request count</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Tokens</strong> — input and output token totals</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Cost</strong> — actual cost per variant</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Errors</strong> — error count and rate</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">Quality</strong> — automated quality score (see below)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Statistical Analysis</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Experiments use a <strong class="text-white/80">z-test</strong> for statistical significance analysis, allowing you to determine when a variant is performing reliably better or worse than the control.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Admin API</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Experiments are managed via <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">/api/prism/admin/experiments/</code>.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Automated Quality Scoring
   
  </h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every request receives an automated <strong class="text-white/80">quality score</strong> from 0 to 100, computed from six signals:</p>
